MUNICIPALITY OF ORMSTOWN
REGULAR SITTING OF THE MUNICIPAL COUNCIL
MONDAY, JULY 6, 2026
AT 5 RUE GALE, ORMSTOWN (QUÉBEC) J0S 1K0

AGENDA
[The document is watermarked "Projet" (draft).]

1. OPENING OF THE SITTING
1.1 Address by the mayor
1.2 General question period (30 minutes)

2. ADOPTION OF THE AGENDA

3. MINUTES
3.1 option [sic — likely "Adoption"] of the minutes of the regular sitting held June 1, 2026;
3.2 Adoption of the minutes of the regular sitting held June 15, 2026.

4. ADMINISTRATION, FINANCE AND PERSONNEL MANAGEMENT
4.1 List of accounts payable as of July 6, 2026;
4.2 Initial borrowing under by-law 117-2019 with the Royal Bank of Canada;
4.3 Appointment of an acting mayor (maire suppléant);
4.4 Awarding of a contract for professional laboratory services for materials quality control;
4.5 Mandate for a group-insurance market study;
4.6 Interim staffing at the public works department;
4.7 Installation and operation of a telecommunications tower and related equipment on lot 6 065 482;
4.8 Office d'habitation du Haut-Saint-Laurent: tabling and adoption of the 2025 financial statements;
4.9 Acceptance of the service offer of Groupe Montpetit — recruitment mandate for the position of clerk (greffier/greffière).

5. NOTICES OF MOTION AND BY-LAWS
5.1 Notice of motion — Draft by-law no. 129-2026 on contract management.

6. MUNICIPAL COUNCIL
No items.

7. PUBLIC WORKS AND TECHNICAL SERVICES
7.1 Purchase of de-icing salt;
7.2 Purchase of A-B 10 abrasive, screenings type (criblure);
7.3 Purchase of A-B 10 abrasive, sand type;
7.4 Mandate for the management of the municipal drinking-water and wastewater facilities to Groupe Hélios, Aquatech division;
7.5 Authorization to call for tenders for the works on rang 3, rang Tullochgorum and the Argyle culvert.

8. FIRE SAFETY
8.1 Fire safety service — tabling of the monthly report for May 2026;

9. URBAN PLANNING AND ENVIRONMENT
9.1 Permits issued — June 2026;
9.2 Minor exemption request — 5 rue Victoria;
9.3 PIIA request — Sign, 12 rue Bridge;
9.4 PIIA request — Sign, 25-27 rue Lambton;
9.5 PIIA request — Sign, 36D rue Lambton;
9.6 Residential construction permit request for multi-unit dwellings on lot 6 411 704;
9.7 PPCMOI request for a 6-dwelling residential project on lot 6 455 729;
9.8 PPCMOI request for off-street parking on a vacant lot for the Royal Canadian Legion;
9.9 Amendment of the subdivision by-law.

10. COMMUNICATION, CULTURE, RECREATION AND COMMUNITY LIFE
10.1 Report on library activities for the month of June;
10.2 Financial assistance request: Projet Communic-Action;
10.3 Letter of support to the Centre de formation de Huntingdon for a funding application.

11. MISCELLANEOUS
No items.

12. QUESTION PERIOD (30 minutes)
Question period on agenda items.

13. CLOSING OF THE SITTING
